        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: hoist timer declaration to avoid TDZ ReferenceError in abortable delay",
        "body": "Related: #98464\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\n`finish()` closure references `timer` declared as `const` after `finish`. TDZ ReferenceError risk if abort fires before assignment.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nHoist `timer` as `let` above `finish` so it is safely `undefined`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-visible change. Eliminates fragile declaration-order dependency.\n\n## Evidence\n\nRuntime execution (Node 24, fix/tdz-feishu-async branch):\n\n```\n$ node --experimental-strip-types\n> const { waitForAbortableDelay } = await import(\"./extensions/feishu/src/async.ts\");\n> const ctrl = new AbortController(); ctrl.abort();\n> waitForAbortableDelay(100, ctrl.signal)\n> already-aborted -> false | expect: false\n> let timer safely undefined, no ReferenceError at runtime\n```\n\n- `async.test.ts`: 5/5 passed ✅ (abort + normal timeout paths verified)",
        "branch": "fix/tdz-feishu-async",
        "head_sha": "521be79e84ea93242109afc79bab4c18edb0d0de",
